This is easily achieved in v9 by using an AbortSignal.

```js
import { globStream } from 'glob'

const getFirstResult = async (patterns, options = {}) => {
  const ac = new AbortController()
  const s = globStream(patterns, { ...options, signal: ac.signal })
  return new Promise((res, rej) =>
    s.once('data', match => {
      res(match)
      ac.abort()
    })
    s.on('error', er => {
      if (!ac.signal.aborted) rej(er)
    })
  })
}
```

Note that in many cases, the specific match you get will be non-deterministic, based on which filesystem call happens to resolve sooner.  For example, if you search for `['a/b/c/*', 'x/y/z/*']`, then it's possible for the second readdir to resolve before the first, resulting in a match in `x/y/z/` rather than a match in `a/b/c/`.

