Using backslashes was never explicitly supported by glob, see the [windows portion of the README](https://github.com/isaacs/node-glob/#windows). My current solution is to resolve paths and then normalize them to forward slashes. See this example:

```js
// assuming the pattern is stored in string variable pattern, and that node's path module has been imported
const normalizedPattern = path.resolve(pattern).split(path.sep).join("/");
glob.sync(normalizedPattern);
```

